    "updated_at": "2013-10-21T18:23:08Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I agree that it is not that obvious, but the (sphinx) author is a configurable and thus, can be set during the nbconvert call. You can get all possible configurable variables with `ipython nbconvert --help-all` \nYou get ...\n\n```\n...\nSphinxTransformer options\n-------------------------\n--SphinxTransformer.author=<Unicode>\n    Default: 'Unknown Author'\n    Author name\n...\n```\n\nSo you can call\n\n```\nipython nbconvert --to latex --SphinxTransformer.author='John Doe' file.ipynb\n```\n\nNote that, in the current master, the latex template is no longer sphinx based (per default), hence, the behavior is slightly different.\n"
  },
